 entrusted with the royal seal, effectively making constituting him the chancellor of the kingdom, the highest member of the royal administration. Louis IX secured his election as bishop of Évreux in 1269. Using the records of Philippe’s work in Reims, Paris, and Évreux, William Chester Jordan reconstructs Philippe’s his career, providing a fascinating portrait of the successes and failures of reform in the thirteenth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aBishopszFrancevBiography. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aChancellor of France.  aEvreux.  aLouis IX of France.  aMiddle Ages.  aParlement.  aPhilippe of Cahors.  aReims.  aarchdeacon.  abishops.  achurch and state.  achurch history.  aenquêteur.  ahistory of religion.  amedieval France.  amorality.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z97831106904530 cprintz978148752461640uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753514840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487535148423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487535148/original  a978-3-11-069045-3  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070473-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  